# Design system sync (required)

Canonical brand guide lives at **`public/design.md`**.

It is served as **raw markdown** at **`https://iswar.me/design.md`** (and locally at `/design.md`). Other agents, designers, and subdomain apps fetch this URL as brand context (like `llms.txt`).

## When you MUST update `public/design.md`

If you change any of the following on this website, update `public/design.md` in the **same PR / commit** so the networked brand doc stays accurate:

- Colours / CSS variables in `src/styles/global.css` (or equivalent tokens)
- Typography (font families, weights, blog vs UI type roles)
- Layout philosophy, spacing, borders, shadows, CTAs, cards, heroes
- Imagery rules (e.g. grayscale amount)
- Motion / interaction patterns that are part of the brand feel
- Logo / wordmark treatment
- Anything that would make PPT, social, or `*.iswar.me` apps look wrong if they followed the old guide

## How to update

1. Edit **`public/design.md` only** (do not invent a second competing guide at repo root).
2. Keep the **blog / Libre Baskerville** voice as the cross-surface typography standard unless the product owner explicitly changes that policy.
3. Refresh tokens, examples, anti-patterns, and the “Source of truth” / checklist sections.
4. Bump or refresh the “last aligned” note at the bottom when the visual system meaningfully changes.

## Do not

- Serve a styled HTML page instead of raw markdown at `/design.md`
- Duplicate the full guide elsewhere and let copies drift
- Change site UI brand and leave `public/design.md` stale
